-- China Construction Bank's Q3 net profit up 5 pct
-- 
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 07:12AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI/HONG KONG, Oct 23(Reuters) - China Construction Bank Corp (CCB) <601939.SS> <0939.HK>, the country's second biggest lender, posted a 5 percent rise in third-quarter net profit on Thursday, in line with expectations.

Net profit rose to 59.64 billion yuan ($9.75 billion) in the quarter, according to the bank's unaudited financial statement  filed on Thursday. Analysts in a Reuters poll had on average predicted a result of 60.2 billion yuan. Its non-performing loan ratio increased to 1.13 percent by the end of September from 1.04 percent at the end of June.